  "local_port": 39496,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at AIG?",
  "response": "As a new employee at American International Group (AIG), there are several things you should know before your first day:\n\n1. Company culture: AIG values integrity, respect, and teamwork. Be prepared to collaborate with colleagues and contribute to a positive work environment.\n\n2. Dress code: AIG typically follows a business casual dress code, but it may vary depending on your specific role and location. When in doubt, it's better to dress more formally on your first day.\n\n3. Arrival time: Arrive a few minutes early to allow time for checking in at the front desk, obtaining your security badge, and familiarizing yourself with the office layout.\n\n4. First-day orientation: AIG usually provides a new employee orientation to introduce you to the company's mission, values, and policies. Be ready to participate actively and ask questions.\n\n5. Required documentation: Bring any necessary identification and work authorization documents for completing your HR paperwork, such as your I-9 form.\n\n6. Technology and tools: You may be provided with a company laptop, phone, and other necessary tools on your first day. Be prepared to set up your devices and learn about the software and systems AIG uses.\n\n7. Meeting your team: You will likely meet your manager and team members on your first day. Be ready to introduce yourself, share a bit about your background, and express your enthusiasm for joining AIG.\n\n8. Training and onboarding: AIG typically has a structured onboarding process to help you get up to speed in your role. Be prepared to participate in training sessions, shadow colleagues, and ask questions as you learn your responsibilities.\n\n9. Benefits and perks: AIG offers a range of benefits, including health insurance, retirement plans, and wellness programs. You'll receive information about these benefits during your orientation and have the opportunity to enroll in them.\n\n10. Networking: Take advantage of your first day to start building relationships with your colleagues. AIG encourages a collaborative environment, so be open to connecting with people from different departments and levels within the organization.\n\nRemember, your first day is just the beginning of your journey at AIG. Stay open-minded, ask questions, and be eager to learn and grow within the company.",
